caption: WOW WOW WOW the food was absolutely amazing! We had the mock fish cakes, kale, quinoa, Mac n cheese (do not pass up on the Mac n cheese, sooo good) and lentils and everything was beyond delicious. Highly recommend! And you can grab a beer from Blue Dogwood Market right next door!

Ordered on Doordash tonight and will definitely order again soon. I had the walnut tacos wrapped in collards (instead of shells) and my husband had the taco supreme plate with chip base (instead of shells). Both had a TON of flavor, were …
Best vegan food I have ever had. So much Flava!
Great food and service!  Highly recommend.
Wonderful plant based food, personable staff, good vibes all around.. it doesn't get better than this!
A really good vegan food, and I didn’t expect it after I saw the place itself. Highly recommend!

We loved this place!!! It’s a bit hard to find but make sure you do (it’s in Blue Dogwood market). Especially if you want vegetarian/vegan food in the area. Delicious, wholesome comfort food! We have to hand it to the friendly owner and staff that are working hard to run this small business
Enjoyed our lunch here today. Staff could not have been more pleasant or attentive.

This place is such a wonderful addition to Valencia County . Everything from the staff , the food, the decor , & the new parking is great . Great prices for top notch meals and drinks . Probably the most beautiful place to have a meal or coffee .
My go-to for plant-based healthy eating.
Yummy, yummy, yummy! This food is so tasty. Always. Please go out and support this Black family owned business. The Sunday Brunch pancakes are especially delicious.
I really wasn't expecting this place to be excellent, but I was pleasantly surprised to find it to be amazing.
Tasty! And I really like the overall laid-back atmosphere. Totally recommend to any plant-based dudes in the Triangle area
The food was delicious!! I tried vegan fish cakes that came with black beans , grits and kale salad. I also orderedvegan mac and cheese. All delicious!! I highly recommend this place.
Love the baked spaghetti and fish cakes! Everything is good though

I want to give Vegan Flava Cafe a #flameon shout out!  I and my fellow sister had planned a luncheon at another vegan restaurant in Durham. Upon our arrival we were informed that it was closed. Being terribly disappointed, we looked up …
Trust me you haven’t had vegan like this before. Loved the new experience.

Wow they don’t call it vegan flava cafe for nothing. The fish cakes were so good and flavorful. Even the rice and the kale salad were to die for. Convenient ordering and pick up, but there’s no way to leave a tip on the emailed invoices.
First time trying this eatery, and were blown away. Everything we ordered was outstanding, and I’m not even Vegan. Potato salad - wow. Kale salad - boom! Tacos - just yum. Eat here.

Best food ever! We so enjoyed our dinner! Very flavorful! We had ordered on line and when we got home received a call that they had by mistake not given us all we had ordered (I am not sure that we would have even noticed sine the portions …
Ultra slow, even small orders takes 35-45 minutes at least.

This was my very first time trying vegan food and I must say the food was absolutely delicious!! Customer service was perfect, I felt very welcomed. Definitely will be back soon. A black owned vegan restaurant that did not disappoint.
Had the jackfruit taco and the walnut protein taco, I’m not even vegan and they were so good!

Fast, Friendly, and Courteous service. Oh...and the Food!! FRESH...DELICIOUS...and let's not forget, NUTRITIOUS!! If I could, I'd just move in there! Save the time of driving from Durham to Chapel Hill! THAT'S...how Good it is!

The food is amazing! The fish cakes were great paired with the quinoa and kale. I’m so happy the food is also organic and non-gmo. Ask for dessert, they also have the best cupcakes, lemon and chocolate! Service was great, respectful of covid and my food was hot and fresh.
Amazing healthy all you could ever want!!!
Whole food meals and very delicious ! The owner is extremely kind , and very appreciative of his customers.  Definitely recommend ! Flavors are delicious !
This tastes every bit as good as it looks!

I would give this establishment 4 and 1/2 Stars. It's definitely worth a try! Although the location is a little different. It has its own appeal. B mock crab / fish cake is excellent. The mac and cheese is good. The quinoa kale salad is …
Service was frankly great. Place is in a great chill atmosphere and the food was amazing. Will come again!
Sorry I took this picture after I started eating! Absolutely delicious.fish cakes, grits, beans and kale salad.

If you are plant based in Chapel Hill/Durham...you MUST give Vegan Flava Cafe a try. It is the best Vegan menu I have tasted in Chapel Hill. Everything I have tried has been absolutely phenomenal! The Sunday brunch is amazing. On top of the great food, the service is second to none. Can't say enough good things.

The two gentlemen were very informative of their menu and was able to shape a dish to accommodate my Dr Sebi alkaline vegan. Oh! I was PLEASANTLY surprised by the chickpea tuna wrap (in a collard)! I'll be back!
Excellent food.
Chickpea tuna over quinoa with Kale delicious.

I had the mock fish cakes brunch with kale salad, black beans, and cheese grits. I added walnut meat on top of my black beans and got a side of chips. This was sooo amazing. One bite in I was like Lord this is unreal how amazing it is. So …

Staff was really nice, but the food was disappointingly bland and took a long time to arrive. I ordered a vegan tunafish salad, which was served on a plate of mixed greens with no dressing. Maybe there are better options on the menu, but this one was pretty dry and flavorless.
I ordered a brunch special with mock fish cakes, kale, cheese grits and black beans. Everything was delicious! I will definitely return.
Love the food and the vibes. Prices are great as well.
Good service and food
Food was flavorful and delicious
Absolutely fabulous! And that's from a carnivore! What a pleasant surprise 👍👏👏👏
Food was delicious! I will definitely be coming back here.

The only knock on this place is their relatively limited selection.  That being said, the food is delicious!
Great selection- prices ok
It was ok but would not go back

The BBQ jackfruit is a winner.
New Chapel Hill location inside Blue Dogwood Market. Tucked into the corner near the back of the parking lot (near where Vespa's used to be). Excellent food and nice vibe inside.
This is a place where all genuine hearts connect. The whole staff and  environment is fantastic!! Food is light and very delicious!! Thank you Vegan Cafe, for all you do.
We ate a late lunch, and everything we tried was wonderful. Great customer service, awesome atmosphere.  Next time we travel through Durham area we will be sure to stop again!

Definetely a "go to" spot for vegans...or for anyone looking to try something "different" good portions and delicious offerings. The Sunday brunch offers pancakes and cheese grits...I recommend the kale salad and the brunch menu.
The fish cakes are incredible!!!
Best vegan food I've had in Durham so far.
Delicious, filling food and friendly staff in a laid-back atmosphere. I definitely will be going back!
Don't expect your socks to be knocked off, but the food is good and more filling than you'll think looking at it
I totally enjoyed my food. I'll definitely be back
Food is very tasty. Made with Love... All of it is delicious. I had the Taco Supreme with jackfruit. Looking forward to going back for more...

Not a vegan, but loved the food. Huge portions and tasted great. Had 'fishcakes,' which are like savory veggie patties with a delicious creamy sauce, along with chana masala. Was served over quinoa, kale salad with a nutty house dressing, and pan fried plantains. The staff are super welcoming too.

Vegan Flava Cafe food is so good. Flavorful, great portions and very filling. The jackfruit bbq, chickpea tuna, fishcakes, walnut tacos and kale salad are all great options. You can get a sampler and try a variety of food. Their prices are very reasonable.

Vegan Flava Cafe is hidden behind the cafeteria off of Guess Road in the plaza with Planet Fitness and the trampoline park. They offer daily hot specials as well as raw food vegan options. It's tasty and healthy stuff. The chana masala is …
Not the fanciest but great food!
Excellent service. The owner takes his time with every customer, discussing the menu and nutrition. He aims to please and is extremely thoughtful.
BLACK OWNED BUSINESS
The food is excellent. Try not to go if you are in a hurry. But the experience is pleasant.
Love love love, great customer service met the OWNER had a full conversation with him great prices and amazing  food
Very healthy while being very tasty
This place is for real vegans! I had Taco Supreme and these were perfectly prepared, bursting with flavor. Pay attention to the specials!  Very impressed!
Great good and amazing service
The kale is something to die for. The lentil soup was so good, this is now one of my top five eateries period.  I am a close friend of Phillip and Gay Butler.
I had their spaghetti today and it was good. I'm really sold on their Sorrell Tea... I'll be getting that by the gallon!!!!
The food was delicious I am coming back!

Vegan flavor unbelievable fish cake cheese grits black beans kale and pancakes that is out of this world. My wife loves it my children love it and it is filling it satisfies my soul a free eating and is gluten free as well.
Vegan. Healthy. Happy. Great Food. Great People. Great Vibes. What more do you want?

Absolutely FANTASTIC food. It doesn't come out incredibly fast, but that is how you know it is made to order! I had the "fish" cakes, red beans, and curried chick peas. All were excellent. The rice in particular was amazing. Also the special cam with plantains which were a delight
Warm and welcoming place w friendly staff and delicious food❤
I am hooked! The food is very flavorful and delicious! My first dish was the fish cakes and they were amazing! Very friendly and peaceful atmosphere! I highly recommend!
The food was delicious and the service was excellent! Would love to visit this place again! The best vegan experience I’ve had in the USA.
My wife and I both loved it.  Everything tasted wonderful.  Very friendly atmosphere.   Great background music!  I had to drive all the way from Carrboro, but I will be back.
First time here, I'm in love. The service was EXCELLENT, the music is relaxing. Nothing better than eating healthy food with so much positive energy around you.

After Celebrating Kwanzaa Day 7, Vegan Flava Cafe opened their doors, (on their normal closed Monday) just to service me and a friend!  I am so happy to say that the Kale/avocado/almond was delicious! Thank you so much for sharing your time with us. Yah-I Ausar Tafari

Hands down the best Vegan place in the triangle! So much love put into the food and the best customer experience I’ve ever had! Will definetly be going be ASAP! If you’re looking for a friendly, delicious, vegan cafe, look no further, you have found it!
Family environment peaceful and the food was great....a delightful spin if your new to vegan cuisine
Nothing special. Portions small. Also not fond of the paper plates and plastic utensils.
